These run script templates are dedicated to code for computing the finite size effect analysis, analyzing the
CDW or SDW ordering averaged over each generation of the honeycomb lattice or hyperbolic lattice.

General conventions:
pval is the p in {p, q} appearing in the Schlafli symbol for hyperbolic lattices (q is assumed to be = 3)
nval_larger is the number of generations for larger system (unlike paper in code we start counting from 1 not 0)
nval_smaller is the number of generations for smaller system (unlike paper in code we start counting from 1 not 0)
vval/uval is the V/U value to do the analysis for, where V/U is the parameter controlling the
strength of the nearest-neighbor Coulomb / onsite Hubbard repulsion interaction

Code assumes all raw_data of relevance is saved from prior SCHF computation
rawdir_larger is the path to the raw data file for the larger system under analysis
rawdir_larger is the path to the raw data file for the smaller system under analysis


